lead_paragraph: No. 9 Georgia overcame a late rally by No. 12 Rutgers to give Coach Andy Landers a 78-69 win yesterday in Norman, Okla., on the day he was named an inductee into the Women’s Basketball Hall of Fame. The Scarlet Knights (0-1) rallied from a 10-point deficit and went ahead, 65-62, with 3 minutes 40 seconds left. But Georgia (1-0) forced turnovers on Rutgers’s next four possessions and scored 10 consecutive points from the free-throw line to regain control.
